alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued November 05 at 9:58PM PST until November 06 at 10:46AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...Forecast flooding changed to Minor severity and increased in duration for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .The river will continue to recede today. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL LATE TOMORROW MORNING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until late tomorrow morning. * IMPACTS...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 10:45 PM PDT Saturday the stage was 54.2 feet. - Recent Activity...The maximum river stage in the 24 hours ending at 10:45 PM PDT Saturday was 56.9 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise to a crest of 54.4 feet late this evening. It will then fall below flood stage late this evening. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 54.3 feet on 01/12/1953. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by Sunday morning at 1000 AM PST.
